cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper introduces a python package for performing computations on manifolds, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on machine learning and the use of Riemannian geometry suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The package's ability to work with images and deep learning frameworks suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely sub-category. The use of Riemannian geometry in optimization and loss functions suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the package's integration with different computing backends and its focus on efficient and user-friendly Riemannian geometry suggests cs.SI (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
